cs.NI, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.OH 

The paper proposes a novel respiratory monitoring system based on ubiquitous off-the-shelf WiFi-enabled devices. It involves the use of signal processing techniques to extract the hidden breathing signal from a noisy WiFi RSS. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the design and implementation of the system, which involves various modules that help reliably extract the hidden breathing signal. This makes cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) another likely category. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques to detect abnormal breathing situations, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another possible category. The system is designed to handle various challenges such as noise elimination, interfering humans, sudden user movements, which makes cs.SY (Systems and Control) another possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the system, which includes respiratory monitoring in various settings, such as hospitals, homes, and workplaces, which makes cs.OH (Other Computer Science) another possible category.
